reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just as described.
reviews.reviewText: Very nice briefcase for my husband. Roomy and nice long shoulder strap.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice overall, no major complaints
reviews.reviewText: The bag overall is pretty nice.There is a ton of room inside for laptop/ipad in the padded section, as well as ample room in the main compartment for notebooks, pads, etc.On the inside are a couple of small pockets on one side along with some pen loops. The pockets are deep, so not ideal for smaller items as getting them out can be a challenge. Also, there is a large pocket on the outside of the padded section, useful for power banks, external HDD, etc.Under the flap are two large pockets that are very deep. And on the back is a zippered pocket, but it seems pretty narrow... useful maybe for travel documents, passports, etc.?The flap closed with two magnetic clasps. Said clasps are somewhat difficult to get to join together... I'm afraid they are not going to properly align and the bag will come flying open at some point. The buckles on the outside are non-functioning... decorative only.My biggest complaint, aside from the clasps, is that there are not more smaller pockets for business cards, etc.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This is excellent quality! Love the pockets! Very sturdy!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice big bag
reviews.reviewText: My husband is really happy to have this bag for his work laptop and riles that he has to transport between his office and home every week. It has a lot of lovely internal pockets for organization. It is clearly a PU bag and not leather- there are a lot of options for genuine leather bags that are not hugely more expensive than this bag but I do think this is a good price for a bag with so many different pockets and sections.My only complaint would be that I wish it had a longer strap for cross body wearing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Soft and lovely leather. Nice high quality buckles and strap. The reason I was attracted to this bag was the nice flat bottom with feet BUT unfortunately it was folded in upon itself and will take months to flatten back out- if ever 😢 I currently have two, gallon jugs of water sitting in mine to try to get it to flatten.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Came and looks like the pics. But the brown leather look in the pic is deceptive. It's obviously vinyl and doesn't look anywhere as dark in color.The closing tabs are not buckles, that's just for show. The tabs actually close with magnetic popper type clips.The inside is as described.All in all an ok bag for the money. You get what you pay for I suppose. Wouldn't order it again though. I would pay more next time to get the ' genuine ' look!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very nice leather briefcase. Good capacity
reviews.reviewText: This briefcase has a very nice look and the leather has a nice feel. The hardware of the bag has both a nice bronzed look and the straps are easily adjustable to the length I want. The clasps create a firm hold and have a nice look as well. The leather has a very nice appearance and provides a very professional look.The briefcase has a good number of pockets and pouches to hold keys, writing utensils and odds and ends that I need for work. The main pouch as a nice pocket to hold my laptop while providing room for other books and paperwork.The briefcase is easy to grab and go and with the nice look, fits into any situation that I have-including work, travel and leisure.Pros: Professional look Good carrying capacity Good durabilityCons: Nothing to report

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very nice, fits a 15.6" laptop and USB-C monitor great
reviews.reviewText: Let's start with the hardware, on this bag, the hardware is excellent and heavy duty. The clasps grab and hold well, and the strap hardware is beefy and strong. I put both my 15.6" laptop, and new 15.6" USB-C monitor in the bag, and they fit great. The front pocket easily holds the adapters. The main compartment has a zipper to close it up, as well as the main flap. The leather on this is very nice and looks good. Inside is roomy, and easily holds my electronics plus notepads, pens, etc. There is also a removable key clip if you want your keys in your bag instead of your pocket.The bottom has small feet for setting the bag down without damaging the bottom, and it stands nicely when filled.
